17#ifndef READCONF_H
18#define READCONF_H
19
20/* Data structure for representing option data. */
21
22#define SSH_MAX_HOSTS_FILES 32
23#define MAX_CANON_DOMAINS 32
24#define PATH_MAX_SUN (sizeof((struct sockaddr_un *)0)->sun_path)
25
26struct allowed_cname {
27 char *source_list;
28 char *target_list;
29};
30
31typedef struct {
32 int forward_agent; /* Forward authentication agent. */
33 int forward_x11; /* Forward X11 display. */
34 int forward_x11_timeout; /* Expiration for Cookies */
35 int forward_x11_trusted; /* Trust Forward X11 display. */
36 int exit_on_forward_failure; /* Exit if bind(2) fails for -L/-R */
37 char *xauth_location; /* Location for xauth program */
38 struct ForwardOptions fwd_opts; /* forwarding options */
39 int pubkey_authentication; /* Try ssh2 pubkey authentication. */
40 int hostbased_authentication; /* ssh2's rhosts_rsa */
41 int challenge_response_authentication;
42#if defined(KRB4) || defined(KRB5)
43 int kerberos_authentication; /* Try Kerberos authentication. */
44#endif
45#if defined(AFS) || defined(KRB5)
46 int kerberos_tgt_passing; /* Try Kerberos TGT passing. */
47#endif
48#ifdef AFS
49 int afs_token_passing; /* Try AFS token passing. */
50#endif
51 /* Try S/Key or TIS, authentication. */
52 int gss_authentication; /* Try GSS authentication */
53 int gss_deleg_creds; /* Delegate GSS credentials */
54 int password_authentication; /* Try password
55 * authentication. */
56 int kbd_interactive_authentication; /* Try keyboard-interactive auth. */
57 char *kbd_interactive_devices; /* Keyboard-interactive auth devices. */
58 int batch_mode; /* Batch mode: do not ask for passwords. */
59 int check_host_ip; /* Also keep track of keys for IP address */
60 int strict_host_key_checking; /* Strict host key checking. */
61 int compression; /* Compress packets in both directions. */
62 int tcp_keep_alive; /* Set SO_KEEPALIVE. */
63 int ip_qos_interactive; /* IP ToS/DSCP/class for interactive */
64 int ip_qos_bulk; /* IP ToS/DSCP/class for bulk traffic */
65 int tcp_rcv_buf; /* user switch to set tcp recv buffer */
66 int tcp_rcv_buf_poll; /* Option to poll recv buf every window transfer */
67 int hpn_disabled; /* Switch to disable HPN buffer management */
68 int hpn_buffer_size; /* User definable size for HPN buffer window */
69
70 SyslogFacility log_facility; /* Facility for system logging. */
71 LogLevel log_level; /* Level for logging. */
72
73 int port; /* Port to connect. */
74 int address_family;
75 int connection_attempts; /* Max attempts (seconds) before
76 * giving up */
77 int connection_timeout; /* Max time (seconds) before
78 * aborting connection attempt */
79 int number_of_password_prompts; /* Max number of password
80 * prompts. */
81 char *ciphers; /* SSH2 ciphers in order of preference. */
82 char *macs; /* SSH2 macs in order of preference. */
83 char *hostkeyalgorithms; /* SSH2 server key types in order of preference. */
84 char *kex_algorithms; /* SSH2 kex methods in order of preference. */
85 char *ca_sign_algorithms; /* Allowed CA signature algorithms */
86 char *hostname; /* Real host to connect. */
87 char *host_key_alias; /* hostname alias for .ssh/known_hosts */
88 char *proxy_command; /* Proxy command for connecting the host. */
89 char *user; /* User to log in as. */
90 int escape_char; /* Escape character; -2 = none */
91
92 u_int num_system_hostfiles; /* Paths for /etc/ssh/ssh_known_hosts */
93 char *system_hostfiles[SSH_MAX_HOSTS_FILES];
94 u_int num_user_hostfiles; /* Path for $HOME/.ssh/known_hosts */
95 char *user_hostfiles[SSH_MAX_HOSTS_FILES];
96 char *preferred_authentications;
97 char *bind_address; /* local socket address for connection to sshd */
98 char *bind_interface; /* local interface for bind address */
99 char *pkcs11_provider; /* PKCS#11 provider */
100 int verify_host_key_dns; /* Verify host key using DNS */
101
102 int num_identity_files; /* Number of files for RSA/DSA identities. */
103 char *identity_files[SSH_MAX_IDENTITY_FILES];
104 int identity_file_userprovided[SSH_MAX_IDENTITY_FILES];
105 struct sshkey *identity_keys[SSH_MAX_IDENTITY_FILES];
106
107 int num_certificate_files; /* Number of extra certificates for ssh. */
108 char *certificate_files[SSH_MAX_CERTIFICATE_FILES];
109 int certificate_file_userprovided[SSH_MAX_CERTIFICATE_FILES];
110 struct sshkey *certificates[SSH_MAX_CERTIFICATE_FILES];
111
112 int add_keys_to_agent;
113 char *identity_agent; /* Optional path to ssh-agent socket */
114
115 /* Local TCP/IP forward requests. */
116 int num_local_forwards;
117 struct Forward *local_forwards;
118
119 /* Remote TCP/IP forward requests. */
120 int num_remote_forwards;
121 struct Forward *remote_forwards;
122 int clear_forwardings;
123
124 /* stdio forwarding (-W) host and port */
125 char *stdio_forward_host;
126 int stdio_forward_port;
127
128 int enable_ssh_keysign;
129 int64_t rekey_limit;
130 int rekey_interval;
131 int none_switch; /* Use none cipher */
132 int none_enabled; /* Allow none to be used */
133 int no_host_authentication_for_localhost;
134 int identities_only;
135 int server_alive_interval;
136 int server_alive_count_max;
137
138 int num_send_env;
139 char **send_env;
140 int num_setenv;
141 char **setenv;
142
143 char *control_path;
144 int control_master;
145 int control_persist; /* ControlPersist flag */
146 int control_persist_timeout; /* ControlPersist timeout (seconds) */
147
148 int hash_known_hosts;
149
150 int tun_open; /* tun(4) */
151 int tun_local; /* force tun device (optional) */
152 int tun_remote; /* force tun device (optional) */
153
154 char *local_command;
155 int permit_local_command;
156 char *remote_command;
157 int visual_host_key;
158
159 int request_tty;
160 int send_version_first;
161
162 int proxy_use_fdpass;
163
164 int num_canonical_domains;
165 char *canonical_domains[MAX_CANON_DOMAINS];
166 int canonicalize_hostname;
167 int canonicalize_max_dots;
168 int canonicalize_fallback_local;
169 int num_permitted_cnames;
170 struct allowed_cname permitted_cnames[MAX_CANON_DOMAINS];
171
172 char *revoked_host_keys;
173
174 int fingerprint_hash;
175
176 int update_hostkeys; /* one of SSH_UPDATE_HOSTKEYS_* */
177
178 char *hostbased_key_types;
179 char *pubkey_key_types;
180
181 char *jump_user;
182 char *jump_host;
183 int jump_port;
184 char *jump_extra;
185
186 char *ignored_unknown; /* Pattern list of unknown tokens to ignore */
187} Options;
188
189#define SSH_CANONICALISE_NO 0
190#define SSH_CANONICALISE_YES 1
191#define SSH_CANONICALISE_ALWAYS 2
192
193#define SSHCTL_MASTER_NO 0
194#define SSHCTL_MASTER_YES 1
195#define SSHCTL_MASTER_AUTO 2
196#define SSHCTL_MASTER_ASK 3
197#define SSHCTL_MASTER_AUTO_ASK 4
198
199#define REQUEST_TTY_AUTO 0
200#define REQUEST_TTY_NO 1
201#define REQUEST_TTY_YES 2
202#define REQUEST_TTY_FORCE 3
203
204#define SSHCONF_CHECKPERM 1 /* check permissions on config file */
205#define SSHCONF_USERCONF 2 /* user provided config file not system */
206#define SSHCONF_FINAL 4 /* Final pass over config, after canon. */
207#define SSHCONF_NEVERMATCH 8 /* Match/Host never matches; internal only */
208
209#define SSH_UPDATE_HOSTKEYS_NO 0
210#define SSH_UPDATE_HOSTKEYS_YES 1
211#define SSH_UPDATE_HOSTKEYS_ASK 2
212
213#define SSH_STRICT_HOSTKEY_OFF 0
214#define SSH_STRICT_HOSTKEY_NEW 1
215#define SSH_STRICT_HOSTKEY_YES 2
216#define SSH_STRICT_HOSTKEY_ASK 3
217
218void initialize_options(Options *);
219void fill_default_options(Options *);
220void fill_default_options_for_canonicalization(Options *);
221int process_config_line(Options *, struct passwd *, const char *,
222 const char *, char *, const char *, int, int *, int);
223int read_config_file(const char *, struct passwd *, const char *,
224 const char *, Options *, int, int *);
225int parse_forward(struct Forward *, const char *, int, int);
226int parse_jump(const char *, Options *, int);
227int parse_ssh_uri(const char *, char **, char **, int *);
228int default_ssh_port(void);
229int option_clear_or_none(const char *);
230void dump_client_config(Options *o, const char *host);
231
232void add_local_forward(Options *, const struct Forward *);
233void add_remote_forward(Options *, const struct Forward *);
234void add_identity_file(Options *, const char *, const char *, int);
235void add_certificate_file(Options *, const char *, int);
236
237#endif /* READCONF_H */
